    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) in Chaste White. This example retains its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting perfect compression and a rock-solid idle. The complex vacuum-actuated boost control system remains factory-spec, delivering a seamless transition through the secondary turbocharger engagement. Underpinned by a lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential, the 50/50 weight distribution provides unmatched turn-in precision. The exterior finish is flawless with no orange peel or oxidation, while the interior features pristine bolstered buckets and original plastics. This is an unmolested survivor with a clean undercarriage and original R1-spec dual oil coolers, offering a definitive, analog driving experience for the discerning collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 3
    },
    {
